$interpreted: Lio: Flutterfly...where on earth did you go?
Lio: It's been by my side for so long...
Lio: As long as somebody nice picks up Flutterfly and becomes his new friend, that's all that matters...
Lio: That way...it won't be lonely, right?
Leah: (You dummy...the lonely one is gonna be you, not Flutterfly.)
Leah: ──Wah!
Lio: Waaaaahhh!!
Lio: ...S-S-Sis?
Leah: Heehee, this place is so hard to find~
Leah: Luckily the guard outside knows me.
Lio: Sis! You came to find me!
Leah: Didn't I say I was gonna come spend the vacation with you?
Leah: Plus, my grades are outstanding, so the Academy gave me more days off as a reward~
Lio: Really? You're so awesome, sis!
Leah: Haha, only the high score part.
Leah: Forget about that. Bro, gotta ask you something.
Leah: Well, what I mentioned in the letter. How's it coming along?
Lio: I...I still don't think that's a good idea...
Leah: Why?
Lio: Angel's taken such good care of me. How could I ask her for that...?
Leah: She's the queen of the Kingdom of the Sun. That amount of curren is nothing to her.
Leah: "Angel, I haven't seen my sister in sooo long. I really want to have a good time with her..."
Leah: Heehee, if it's you who does the begging, we can definitely get an all-expenses-paid vacation at a luxury hotel.
Leah: The perfect plan. So perfect it scares me~
Lio: I...I can't do it...sis!
Leah: Alright, fine. Ears that long and you still don't listen. Maybe you just don't want to go on vacation with me?
Lio: No way...I mean, Angel's not even in town.
Leah: ...Not in town?
Lio: Yeah, Angel said she's got some official business to attend to. She told me to stay in town for a couple days.
Leah: You mean...look after her house?
Lio: ...It's fine. She's the queen. Everybody relies on her. I'm happy to help.
Lio: Plus...my sis came to see me. I won't get nervous.
Lio: ...Sis?
Leah: ...Oh, well if the queen's not even here, I guess I can just flush my plan down the toilet...
？？？: Did somebody mention waterrrr!?
Jerome: General! Calm down, please!
Fredrica: No matter what, no one is permitted to mention anything related to water in front of me!
Fredrica: NO ONE!!!!
Leah: That voice sounds familiar...it's coming from there!
Lio: Ah! Sis! You can't go in there!
Leah: Oh, it's an old.............graduate of the Rune Academy?
Fredrica: I absolutely did not hear incorrectly. Somebody mentioned a toilet, and a toilet has water! Who dares do such a thing?
Leah: It was my brother, Fredrica~
Lio: Sis!?
Fredrica: Okay then, so it was you?
Jerome: General, that's enough!
Jerome: The queen gave you an important mission. Quit whining and get to work!
Leah: Important mission?
Lio: Ah, Angel mentioned it to me before she left...
Lio: She was worried about the reconstruction of Atlas, so she wants General Lucien to bring food and supplies to Nigel and them.
Jerome: Apologies. You must be Young Lio's sister, Miss Leah. Is that correct?
Jerome: It has been some time since the queen and the demihumans last parted. She wanted to better understand the situation in Atlas...
Leah: Understand?
Jerome: ...And provide assistance.
Jerome: That is the important mission I was referring to.
Leah: Huh? So that's what's going on...
Leah: I thought it was some conspiracy or something. Boringgg~
Lio: Sis! How could you speak about Angel like that!?
Jerome: ......Indeed.
Lio: General Lucien doesn't want to go, but Angel said that she already used all her vacation days.
Lio: If she doesn't work, it's going to get taken out of next month's salary...
Jerome: My apologies...as an officer, it's on me if the general does not act as she ought to.
Jerome: ...So!
Jerome: General, forget about that outfit that shows no sense of shame, and take back your responsibilities as General of the Kingdom of the Sun!
Leah: Outfit?
Leah: That...is considered clothing?
Fredrica: It's not just a piece of clothing!
Fredrica: This was designed by the general herself; this is swimwear apparel...by Carterwell.
Fredrica: It's the hottest, newest fashion this summer!
Lio: If General Lucien so much as sees that outfit, she won't want to do anything. She'll just shout that she wants to go play in the water...
Fredrica: That boy knows nothing. Summer's short for chicks, we've got to take advantage of the season for catching a good man!
Fredrica: Aaaah~Whatta ya think, handsome?
Fredrica: This slippery, exquisite, bouncy white fabric suits me well, don't you think?
Jerome: Yes, it suits you well, General.
Fredrica: Heehee, good eyes~
Fredrica: All you need to do is close your eyes a bit. Maybe you can see what I look like when I put~it~on...
Jerome: In any case, before you finish your work, I, Jerome Muca, will not close both of my eyes.
Jerome: You'll have no chance to loaf on the job. Now please, accept your fate!
Fredrica: Hmph!
Jerome: I know what you've been planning all along. Don't you forget, I'm your officer!
Fredrica: Oh shut it! I didn't get my chance at Maple Lake and I'm not letting this pass me by!
Fredrica: Even though it's you, I'm not letting you stop me!!
Lio: Sis, wait for me just a second, okay?
Lio: I must stop General Lucien...
Leah: Eh...why?
Lio: Angel worked so hard to complete her responsibilities. I-I think that General Lucien should also...
Jerome: Young Lio speaks the truth!
Fredrica: Damn, ganging up on me, are you!?
Fredrica: Hey Bunny-boo, didn't see you there?
Jerome: ...You just spoke with Miss Leah.
Fredrica: Wonderful. Well, honey. These two boys are picking on me~
Fredrica: Hurry up and help me teach them a lesson!
Leah: Um~but I don't wanna make the queen mad~
Leah: Angel has taken such good care of my brother. How could I make her upset...
Lio: Sis!
Fredrica: A flawless strategy.
Fredrica: Well then. Since you're my girl, if you help me, I'll take you on vacation...
Fredrica: ──Everything is on me! Whatta you say?
Leah: It's a deal!
Leah: For my summer fantasy vacation, y'all better wise up!
Lio: ...*sob*...ridiculous...
Jerome: Despicable...
Fredrica: Sorry, handsome~just deal with it, will ya?
Fredrica: Bunny-boo let's go!
Leah: Okay~you're the best~
Lio: J-Jerome...?
Jerome: I can't...I can't just give up like that! General! In any case...listen to my last words!
Fredrica: Handsome, no one likes a know-it-all~
Fredrica: Don't be so stiff. Learn how to flow like water, like me~
Jerome: ...Ugh...
Jerome: ...Learn from the general...?
Jerome: This is a letter written by Queen Angelia herself. Look, the authentic Carlos stamp is right here.
Fredrica: Even if you bring the queen into this, I...
Jerome: Orders from the queen, so long as the general completes this mission...
Jerome: ...she'll be awarded with seven days vacation time.
Fredrica: S-Seven days!?
Jerome: Not bad, and...
Fredrica: And what?
Jerome: The letter says those days... are paid vacation days...
Jerome: ...and that you can apply for a vacation subsidy.
Fredrica: .........
Leah: F-Fredrica?
Fredrica: As the loyal general of the Kingdom of the Sun, it is obviously our duty to complete our mission~
Fredrica: Handsome, prepare food and supplies as I order. We're heading to Atlas~
Jerome: Yes, ma'am. General Lucien, I'll get on it immediately.
Fredrica: Yes. And~
Fredrica: ...Does the subsidy cover moisturizing sunscreen lotion?
